        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Monitor warning and critical macOS memory-pressure events.\n- Evict only idle OpenAI dashboard WebViews, preserving active refreshes.\n- Release free malloc pages from a detached utility task so pressure handling does not block the main actor.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `swift test --filter OpenAIDashboardWebViewCacheTests`: 22 tests passed.\n- Focused test/log proof: shared cache changed from `before=2` to `after=1`, `evicted=1`, while the busy WebView remained cached.\n- Thread regression test proves malloc relief executes off the main thread.\n- Fresh debug executable live proof via `com.steipete.codexbar.debug.simulateMemoryPressure`: seeded one idle and one busy WebView; unified log reported `before=2 after=1 evicted=1`; app remained running.\n- `make check`: passed; SwiftLint found 0 violations in 1,145 files.\n- `autoreview --mode local --stream-engine-output`: clean, no actionable findings, confidence 0.86.\n- Fresh packaged app built, signed for development, launched, and remained running.\n\n## Review\n\n- Rebased onto current `main`.\n- Added contributor changelog credit.\n- Maintainer repair: `4c6ce6c8` moves malloc relief off the main actor.\n",
